</specimenCount>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,729,470,492]" box="[151,729,470,492]" pageId="6" pageNumber="965">D i s t r i b u t i o n: ThisspeciesisknownfromPeru.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1058,507,559]" pageId="6" pageNumber="965">
E t y m o l o g y: The trivial name, 
<emphasis box="[555,610,507,528]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="965">nolus</emphasis>
, is a Latin noun that stems from 
<emphasis box="[980,1025,507,528]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="965">nola</emphasis>
(= bell); with reference to the shape of the pronotum.
</paragraph>
